hh3cIsdnMib.name: hh3cIsdnMib
hh3cIsdnMib.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip: 100085
hh3cIsdnMib.description: This file describes the H3C MIB implementation of ISDN

hh3cChanbIsdnTable.name: hh3cChanbIsdnTable
hh3cChanbIsdnTable.description: This table is used to describe the router's B Channels infomation

hh3cChanbIsdnIf.name: hh3cChanbIsdnIf
hh3cChanbIsdnIf.description: this object is used to describe the virtual interface value associated with one neighbor.

hh3cChanbIsdnPermit.name: hh3cChanbIsdnPermit
hh3cChanbIsdnPermit.description: this object is used to describe the call permissions.

hh3cChanbIsdnAddr.name: hh3cChanbIsdnAddr
hh3cChanbIsdnAddr.description: this object is used to descirbe the call address by which we call one nieghbor.

hh3cChanbIsdnCallerAddr.name: hh3cChanbIsdnCallerAddr
hh3cChanbIsdnCallerAddr.description: this object is used to describe the callser address which will be known by B channels.

hh3cChanbIsdnCallType.name: hh3cChanbIsdnCallType
hh3cChanbIsdnCallType.description: this object is used to describe that whether it is an incoming call or an outging call.

hh3cChanbIsdnInfoType.name: hh3cChanbIsdnInfoType
hh3cChanbIsdnInfoType.description: this object is used to describe the information type on the call

hh3cChanbIsdnState.name: hh3cChanbIsdnState
hh3cChanbIsdnState.description: this object is used to manage the call by NMS

hh3cChanbIsdnCallFreeReason.name: hh3cChanbIsdnCallFreeReason
hh3cChanbIsdnCallFreeReason.description: this object is used to describe the reason why last call is cleard

hh3cChanbIsdnCallFreeCode.name: hh3cChanbIsdnCallFreeCode
hh3cChanbIsdnCallFreeCode.description: this object is used to describe the reason code for the last call down.

hh3cChanbIsdnCallAccept.name: hh3cChanbIsdnCallAccept
hh3cChanbIsdnCallAccept.description: this object is used to describe the accepted call number from the B channels

hh3cChanbIsdnCallReject.name: hh3cChanbIsdnCallReject
hh3cChanbIsdnCallReject.description: this object is used to describe the refused call number from B channels .

hh3cChanbIsdnCallSuccess.name: hh3cChanbIsdnCallSuccess
hh3cChanbIsdnCallSuccess.description: this object is used to describe the successful call number to B channels after system restart.

hh3cChanbIsdnCallFailure.name: hh3cChanbIsdnCallFailure
hh3cChanbIsdnCallFailure.description: this object is used to describe the failing call number to B channels after system restart

hh3cChanbIsdnMaxKeepTime.name: hh3cChanbIsdnMaxKeepTime
hh3cChanbIsdnMaxKeepTime.description: This object is used to descirbe the maximum duration time in milliseconds.

hh3cChanbIsdnLastKeepTime.name: hh3cChanbIsdnLastKeepTime
hh3cChanbIsdnLastKeepTime.description: this object is used to describe the last call duration time in milliseconds

hh3cChanbIsdnLastCallTime.name: hh3cChanbIsdnLastCallTime
hh3cChanbIsdnLastCallTime.description: this object is used to describe the sysUpTime after last call attempt was made.

hh3cChanbTrapEnable.name: hh3cChanbTrapEnable
hh3cChanbTrapEnable.description: This object is used to control sending trap

hh3cQ931CallSetupTrapEnable.name: hh3cQ931CallSetupTrapEnable
hh3cQ931CallSetupTrapEnable.description: This object is used to control sending callsetup trap.

hh3cQ931CallClearTrapEnable.name: hh3cQ931CallClearTrapEnable
hh3cQ931CallClearTrapEnable.description: This object is used to control sending callclear trap

hh3cQ931IsdnTable.name: hh3cQ931IsdnTable
hh3cQ931IsdnTable.description: This table describes B channel information for the use of Q931

hh3cQ931IsdnEntry.name: hh3cQ931IsdnEntry
hh3cQ931IsdnEntry.description: A B channel entry in the Q931.

hh3cQ931IsdnOpIndex.name: hh3cQ931IsdnOpIndex
hh3cQ931IsdnOpIndex.description: Index of the B ISDN channel interface managed by Q93

hh3cQ931IsdnLastCalled.name: hh3cQ931IsdnLastCalled
hh3cQ931IsdnLastCalled.description: This object describes the called ISDN number. When an outgoing call is established successfully, the value of this node is the call number of this device, otherwise the value is null string

hh3cQ931IsdnLastCalling.name: hh3cQ931IsdnLastCalling
hh3cQ931IsdnLastCalling.description: This object describes the calling ISDN number. When an incoming call is established successfully, the value of this node is the call number of peer device, otherwise the value is null string.

hh3cQ931IsdnLastCauseDisc.name: hh3cQ931IsdnLastCauseDisc
hh3cQ931IsdnLastCauseDisc.description: This object describes last cause of disconnection. In hh3cQ931IsdnCallClear trap, the value of this node is the reason of disconnection, this node is only valid for hh3cQ931IsdnCallClear trap, the value of this node is unknown in other situation. unknown: unknown error. normCallClr: normal call clearing. noRouteToTransNet: no route to specified transit network. noRouteToDest: no route to destination. switchEquCongest: switching equipment congestion. netOutofOrder: network out of order.

hh3cQ931IsdnCallDirection.name: hh3cQ931IsdnCallDirection
hh3cQ931IsdnCallDirection.description: This object describes the direction of the current call.

hh3cQ931IsdnCallTimeOpen.name: hh3cQ931IsdnCallTimeOpen
hh3cQ931IsdnCallTimeOpen.description: This object describes the start time of this call. start time is the time of an existent call that has just been established.

hh3cQ931IsdnCallTimeClose.name: hh3cQ931IsdnCallTimeClose
hh3cQ931IsdnCallTimeClose.description: This object describes the close time of this call. This node is only vaild for hh3cQ931IsdnCallClear trap. In other situation the value of this node is zero. In hh3cQ931IsdnCallClear trap, this node provides the time of an existent call that the call has just been cleared.

hh3cLapdIsdnTable.name: hh3cLapdIsdnTable
hh3cLapdIsdnTable.description: This table is used to describe the config of ISDN D channel.

hh3cLapdIsdnIf.name: hh3cLapdIsdnIf
hh3cLapdIsdnIf.description: This object is used to describe the D channel interface value associated with one neighbor.

hh3cLapdIsdnProtocol.name: hh3cLapdIsdnProtocol
hh3cLapdIsdnProtocol.description: This object is used to describe the protocol D channel applied. For E1, the protocol may be dss1, qsig, etsi. For T1, the protocol may be ess5, ansi, att, dss1, etsi, ni2, ntt, qsig. For BRI, the protocol may be ansi, dss1, etsi, ni, ntt.

hh3cLapdIsdnIfMode.name: hh3cLapdIsdnIfMode
hh3cLapdIsdnIfMode.description: The physical interface mode. For TE mode, the value of this object is userSide. For NT mode, the value of this object is networkSide.

hh3cLapdIsdnLinkStatus.name: hh3cLapdIsdnLinkStatus
hh3cLapdIsdnLinkStatus.description: The operational status of this interface: inactive all layers are inactive. l1Active layer 1 is activated, layer 2 datalink not established. l2Active layer 1 is activated, layer 2 datalink established.

hh3cLapdStatusTrapEnable.name: hh3cLapdStatusTrapEnable
hh3cLapdStatusTrapEnable.description: This object is used to control sending hh3cLapdIsdnStatusChange trap.

hh3cChanbIsdnCall.name: hh3cChanbIsdnCall
hh3cChanbIsdnCall.description: When one call is setup ,cleard or determined , the trap is sent to NMS

hh3cQ931IsdnCallSetup.name: hh3cQ931IsdnCallSetup
hh3cQ931IsdnCallSetup.description: This trap/inform is sent to the manager whenever a call is established successfully.

hh3cQ931IsdnCallClear.name: hh3cQ931IsdnCallClear
hh3cQ931IsdnCallClear.description: This trap/inform is sent to the manager under the following conditions: - an existent call is normally cleared. - an existent call is determined to have ultimately failed, and has been cleared. - the existent call is cleared when the BRI/PRI port is down. - the existent call is cleared when the dialer rule is down.

hh3cLapdIsdnStatusChange.name: hh3cLapdIsdnStatusChange
hh3cLapdIsdnStatusChange.description: This trap/inform is sent to the manager whenever the D-channel of an interface changes state.
